body.content:
Donsciba.com,

Hope this email finds you well.

I’m a website designer with more than ten years of experience in working
with multiple platforms and technologies involving website design and
development.

I would like to share with you a few insights which most of the web
developers and web owners miss out on in early days,that impacts them
greatly afterwards.

Website *Bounce Rate*: It’s one of the major factors that contributes to
website performance. As per Google standard only two percent of online
visitors stay at a website or home page if they find it interesting. Hence,
grabbing attention from the first few seconds is the challenge.

A website with no *call to action elements* almost makes the task half
done; we can ensure not only visitors, rather better call to action
elements which will encourage phone calls and emails for the website.

How can we forget a *responsive design*, which is a mandate now for any
search engine update? Recent update from Google made a strict policy to
five priority to websites having better mobile codes than counterparts.

Again, we can’t ignore search engines. We will ensure your design is *search
engine friendly and optimized* with best keywords.

I’m not talking about some cheap tricks. It’s pure technical and
informative to make your website visible.

Our expertise in cross platform and cross domain makes us stand out in a
crowd. Our skill sets are mapped to CMS like WordPress, Joomla, Magento
etc. web languages and custom platforms like PHP, Java & .Net. With Basic
skills on HTML and bootstrap CSS is of essence.

Please reply us back for more information on prices and references to start
your new website design.



Regards

*Cheryl Griffin* (BDM)
